[2026-03-10T15:59:15Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015pZi4ZVZa2mMjQmf281ZfF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Next Features Design\n     2→\n     3→Date: 2026-03-03\n     4→\n     5→This document captures the design for the five features listed in PROJECT.md:\n     6→Orchestrator, Indicator Lights, Web Dashboard, Log Contents, and Container Deletion.\n     7→\n     8→## 1. Orchestrator\n     9→\n    10→**Goal:** Automate work dispatch — pull ready tasks from a task tracker, generate\n    11→prompts via LLM, kick off workflow runs, and manage the merge queue for landing\n    12→completed work.\n    13→\n    14→**Location:** Built into `cloched` (no new binary).\n    15→\n    16→**Components:**\n    17→\n    18→### TaskTracker Port\n    19→\n    20→New interface `ports.TaskTracker`:\n    21→\n    22→```go\n    23→type Task struct {\n    24→    ID          string\n    25→    Title       string\n    26→    Description string\n    27→    Labels      []string\n    28→    Priority    int\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→type TaskTracker interface {\n    32→    ListReady(ctx context.Context, project string) ([]Task, error)\n    33→    Claim(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n    34→    Complete(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n    35→    Fail(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n    36→}\n    37→```\n    38→\n    39→First adapter: Beads. Future adapters: Jira, Linear, GitHub Issues.\n    40→\n    41→Tasks returned by `ListReady` are ordered by priority (highest first).\n    42→\n    43→### PromptGenerator\n    44→\n    45→Takes a `Task` and project context, calls the project's configured LLM to generate\n    46→a prompt suitable for the workflow. The generated prompt is passed to the workflow run\n    47→as the `--prompt` argument.\n    48→\n    49→### Orchestration Loop\n    50→\n    51→Event-driven, triggers on:\n    52→1. Daemon startup — check all projects for ready work.\n    53→2. Run completion — after a run finishes, check the completed run's project for more work.\n    54→3. `cloche loop` CLI command — manual trigger, checks all projects.\n    55→\n    56→On trigger:\n    57→1. For each registered project with orchestration enabled:\n    58→2. Query task tracker for ready work (priority-ordered).\n    59→3. Check in-flight run count against per-project concurrency limit.\n    60→4. For each available slot: claim the highest-priority task, generate prompt, dispatch run.\n    61→\n    62→### Configuration\n    63→\n    64→Per-project in `.cloche/config.toml` (or similar):\n    65→\n    66→```toml\n    67→[orchestration]\n    68→enabled = true\n    69→tracker = \"beads\"\n    70→concurrency = 1\n    71→workflow = \"develop\"\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→### Concurrency\n    75→\n    76→Per-project limits. Project A with limit 2 and project B with limit 1 can have up to\n    77→3 runs in-flight simultaneously.\n    78→\n    79→### Merge Queue\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1833ddb6-4c99-47f1-b217-57b1c898f9f1","uuid":"9c6a6fba-365b-4b9d-a845-4bbb8daf6446","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md","content":"# Next Features Design\n\nDate: 2026-03-03\n\nThis document captures the design for the five features listed in PROJECT.md:\nOrchestrator, Indicator Lights, Web Dashboard, Log Contents, and Container Deletion.\n\n## 1. Orchestrator\n\n**Goal:** Automate work dispatch — pull ready tasks from a task tracker, generate\nprompts via LLM, kick off workflow runs, and manage the merge queue for landing\ncompleted work.\n\n**Location:** Built into `cloched` (no new binary).\n\n**Components:**\n\n### TaskTracker Port\n\nNew interface `ports.TaskTracker`:\n\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n    ID          string\n    Title       string\n    Description string\n    Labels      []string\n    Priority    int\n}\n\ntype TaskTracker interface {\n    ListReady(ctx context.Context, project string) ([]Task, error)\n    Claim(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n    Complete(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n    Fail(ctx context.Context, taskID string) error\n}\n```\n\nFirst adapter: Beads. Future adapters: Jira, Linear, GitHub Issues.\n\nTasks returned by `ListReady` are ordered by priority (highest first).\n\n### PromptGenerator\n\nTakes a `Task` and project context, calls the project's configured LLM to generate\na prompt suitable for the workflow. The generated prompt is passed to the workflow run\nas the `--prompt` argument.\n\n### Orchestration Loop\n\nEvent-driven, triggers on:\n1. Daemon startup — check all projects for ready work.\n2. Run completion — after a run finishes, check the completed run's project for more work.\n3. `cloche loop` CLI command — manual trigger, checks all projects.\n\nOn trigger:\n1. For each registered project with orchestration enabled:\n2. Query task tracker for ready work (priority-ordered).\n3. Check in-flight run count against per-project concurrency limit.\n4. For each available slot: claim the highest-priority task, generate prompt, dispatch run.\n\n### Configuration\n\nPer-project in `.cloche/config.toml` (or similar):\n\n```toml\n[orchestration]\nenabled = true\ntracker = \"beads\"\nconcurrency = 1\nworkflow = \"develop\"\n```\n\n### Concurrency\n\nPer-project limits. Project A with limit 2 and project B with limit 1 can have up to\n3 runs in-flight simultaneously.\n\n### Merge Queue\n","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":269}}}
